# Development Rule

Whenever building any component or implementing functional logic that requires
the current project information (e.g., `project_id`, `Project`, `ProjectMember`, etc.),
you **must always** get this data from the `RootContext`.

The following interfaces represent data that is already fully available
through the application's RootContext and **should never be fetched using
query parameters**:

Also make sure there should no unused code left in the code.

```ts

export interface IUser {
  id: number;
  created_at: Date;
  update_at: Date;
  email: string;
  first_name: string;
  last_name: string;
  company: string;
  project_members: ProjectMember[];
  _count: {
    campaigns: number;
  };
}

export interface ProjectMember {
  id: number;
  created_at: Date;
  update_at: Date;
  user_id: number;
  role_id: number;
  project_id: number;
  project: Project;
}

export interface Project {
  id: number;
  created_at: Date;
  update_at: Date;
  name: string;
  company: string;
  app_store_link: string;
  play_store_link: string;
  website: string;
  timezone: string | null;
}

```


# Always check the component before using the component.